# linkify-svelte

Svelte 5 component for [Linkify](http://linkify.js.org/). Automatically detects URLs, email addresses, and other link types, and renders them as anchor tags.

## Installation

Install from npm

```bash
npm install linkifyjs linkify-svelte
```

or with other package managers

```bash
pnpm add linkifyjs linkify-svelte
bun add linkifyjs linkify-svelte
```

## Usage

```svelte
<script>
  import Linkify from 'linkify-svelte';

  const content = 'For help with GitHub.com, please email support@github.com';
</script>

<Linkify text={content} />
```

This will render:

```html
For help with <a href="http://github.com">GitHub.com</a>, please email <a href="mailto:support@github.com">support@github.com</a>
```

## Props

| Prop | Type | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| `text` | `string` | **Required.** The text content to parse for links |
| `options` | `Opts` | Linkify options (see [Options documentation](https://linkify.js.org/docs/options.html)) |
| `render` | `Snippet` | Custom render snippet for link elements |

## Examples

### Basic Usage

```svelte
<script>
  import Linkify from 'linkify-svelte';
</script>

<Linkify text="Check out https://example.com for more info." />
```

### With Options

```svelte
<script>
  import Linkify from 'linkify-svelte';

  const options = {
    target: '_blank',
    rel: 'noopener noreferrer',
    className: 'external-link'
  };
</script>

<Linkify text="Visit github.com today!" options={options} />
```

### Custom Link Rendering

Use the `render` snippet to customize how links are rendered:

```svelte
<script>
  import Linkify from 'linkify-svelte';
</script>

<Linkify text="Contact us at hello@example.com">
  {#snippet render({ tagName, attributes, content })}
    <a href={attributes.href} class="custom-link">
      {content}
    </a>
  {/snippet}
</Linkify>
```

### With Hashtags and Mentions

Install additional plugins:

```bash
npm install linkify-plugin-hashtag linkify-plugin-mention
```

```svelte
<script>
  import Linkify from 'linkify-svelte';
  import 'linkify-plugin-hashtag';
  import 'linkify-plugin-mention';

  const options = {
    formatHref: {
      hashtag: (href) => `https://twitter.com/hashtag/${href.substring(1)}`,
      mention: (href) => `https://twitter.com${href}`
    }
  };
</script>

<Linkify
  text="Follow @anthropic and check out #AI"
  options={options}
/>
```

### Newline to Break

Convert newlines to `<br>` tags:

```svelte
<script>
  import Linkify from 'linkify-svelte';

  const content = `Line 1
Line 2
https://example.com`;

  const options = {
    nl2br: true
  };
</script>

<Linkify text={content} options={options} />
```

## Options

The `options` prop accepts standard [Linkify options](https://linkify.js.org/docs/options.html) without event:

- `defaultProtocol` - Protocol for URLs without one (default: `'http'`)
- `target` - Link target attribute (e.g., `'_blank'`)
- `rel` - Link rel attribute
- `className` - CSS class for links
- `nl2br` - Convert newlines to `<br>` tags
- `truncate` - Truncate long URLs
- `format` - Custom format function for link text
- `formatHref` - Custom format function for href
- `validate` - Validation function to filter links
- `ignoreTags` - Tags to ignore when parsing
- `render` - Custom render options per link type

